============================================================
STEP D: Common Bug Checklist
============================================================
=== Manual Checklist ===

[ ] Double rotation of q/k?
    - Check if model already applies RoPE internally
    - Our patch replaces inv_freq, so model still does the rotation
    - Should be OK if we only patch inv_freq

[ ] Cache being re-roped?
    - With nohup fresh model load, KV cache should be fresh
    - Check if past_key_values causes issues

[ ] rotary_dim pairing error?
    - LLaMA uses full rotary_dim = head_dim
    - Check if split is correct (first half, second half)

[ ] position_ids broadcast wrong?
    - position_ids should be (batch, seq) or (seq,)
    - HuggingFace handles this internally

[ ] sigmoid parameterization issue?
    - positions * 100 creates values: 0, 100, 200, ... 6400
    - steepness=10/T = 10/100000 = 0.0001
    - sigmoid(0.0001 * 6400 - 50000) ≈ sigmoid(-49360) ≈ 0
    - sigmoid(0.0001 * 0 - 50000) ≈ sigmoid(-50000) ≈ 0
    - ALL sigmoid outputs ≈ 0, so inv_freq ≈ inv_freq_min = 1e-6!

!!! BUG IDENTIFIED !!!
The sigmoid parameterization is wrong:
- positions * 100 makes the range way too large
- mid = T/2 = 50000, but positions*100 only goes to ~6400
- sigmoid(x - 50000) where x in [0, 6400] is ALWAYS near 0
- Result: ALL inv_freq ≈ 1e-6 (minimum), destroying the model!

FIX: Remove the '*100' factor, use proper scaling

